article:
The State of Georgia is divided into 159 counties. Under the Georgia State
Constitution, all of its counties are granted home rule to deal with problems
that are purely local in nature. Also, seven consolidated city-counties have
been established in Georgia: Athens -- Clarke County, Augusta -- Richmond
County, Columbus -- Muscogee County, Georgetown -- Quitman County, Statenville
-- Echols County, Macon -- Bibb County, and Cusseta -- Chattahoochee County.
